Job Specification:
  Plan and schedule projects, estimate time and materials, supervise subordinates, maintain records  and files and prepare reports.
 Plan and supervise the work of electricians
 Plan and estimate electrical jobs.
 Maintain records on electrical jobs and assign to appropriate personnel.
 Assist  in  coordinating  job  assignments  with  the  other  trades,  e.g.,  outfittings, carpenters
 Assist Naval Arch on electrical drawings and converting single line drawings to detail drawings.
 Maintain knowledge of electrical materials in warehouse.
 Advise and assist Project Managers of technical problems concerned with installation, modification and repair of electrical assignments.
 Recommend procedure revisions when necessary to fully utilize assigned personnel and equipment.
  Determine procedures for maintenance, installation, modification and repair of electrical assignments.
 Inspect  work  to  ensure  compliance  with  standard  procedures  and  electrical assignments.
 Examine electrical services for proper working procedures.
 Perform related work as required.

Person Specification

  Minimum Higher NITEC in Electronics Engineering or Diploma in Electrical Engineering or related field/discipline
  At least 5 years of working experience preferably in Marine Industry
  Good interpersonal, communication and negotiation skills
  Possess valid driving licence is of advantageous
  Graduation from high school supplemented by an appropriate apprenticeship training program and extensive electrical system maintenance experience and some supervisory experience. 
